God grant me the serenity to accept the people I cannot change, the courage to change the one I can, and the wisdom to know it's me. ~Author Unknown
I am mom to the beautiful Maddy, a voracious reader, an internet junkie, and I work at my local MRA as the Family Representative for IDD Services and the HCS medicaid waiver program. (Disclaimer: All opinions expressed by me on FB are my own, and are not representative of those of my employer!) I have a sweet but spoiled mini dachshund named Buddy. I am a simple woman with a complicated inner life. I was a migraineur (with over 20 migraines per month, on average) for over 6 years, but that all ended 9/3/09 and I am loving my life right now! I'm finding my way into the world again, and it's such a blessing. I'm gluten intolerant (it was the cause of my migraines!) and low-carbing for weight loss. I've lost over 125 pounds since 8/31/09! I'm a proud single mama. I strive for grace under pressure, daily laughter, and and doing the right thing ~ always. I may be going through hell right now, but I will keep going. I know when things settle down again that my life will feel even more beautiful and precious for having survived the storms of the last year. I believe that adversity leads to personal growth and that personal growth leads to community growth...that it is the responsibility of every person to make her corner of the world a better place. (updated 4/11)
